	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Let me begin by thanking you guys for your feedback, it is much appreciated.<br /><br />The schematics I used was the buggy Electronix Corp ones for the NES-001.  I do not doubt there are errors, but I have found using this method described works.  The 10uf electrolytic capacitor right before the 330ohm resistor causes no video output, so I just omitted it.  I do not know how it works.  I haven't disassembled my NES (again) to check the schematic.  Last night I traced the Twin Famicom's AV circuit, and I will be attempting it next.  I have attached it here.  D1 is mis-labeled because I cannot identify the diode part number.

		
